The paper deals with interactive learning algorithms that involve human-machine interaction, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the problem of content search, which is a variant of the nearest neighbor search problem, and involves the use of dissimilarity metrics, which are topics that fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes two algorithms that locate the target object in a database, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses experiments that validate the performance of the proposed algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
